tmjos-installer (1.3.4-2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Substitui ubiquity.svg pelo logo TMJOs nos 6 sizes hicolor
    (16/22/24/32/48/64). Top bar do GNOME durante o install agora
    mostra logo TMJOs em vez de logo Ubuntu.
  * Vendor script gera tmjos-ubiquity.svg via SVG wrapper com
    TMJOs_Logo_Rounded.png embedded em base64 (128x128).
    Single SVG cobre todos os 6 sizes via symlinks.
  * postinst dpkg-divert idempotente nos 6 paths + symlink pro
    nosso SVG + gtk-update-icon-cache pra GNOME pegar imediato.
  * postrm reverte tudo em remove/purge.
  * Backlog v1.3.5+: partitioner icons (install/manual/reinstall/
    sidebyside) — aguardando assets Nano Banana TMJOs neon.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Tue, 12 May 2026 09:30:00 -0300

tmjos-installer (1.3.4-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Replace ubiquity's default "Installation complete" image
    (/usr/share/ubiquity/pixmaps/ubuntu_installed.png — the orange
    foxes+crown 234x165 PNG) with the TMJOs Rounded logo, fitted
    via ImageMagick to match the exact dimensions of the original.
  * Implementation: dpkg-divert in postinst (reversible). Our
    branded image lives in /usr/share/tmjos-installer/ and is
    symlinked into the ubiquity path.
  * postrm undoes the divert on package removal.
  * Build dep: imagemagick (used by vendor-installer.sh to resize
    the source logo before .deb assembly).

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 14:00:00 -0300

tmjos-installer (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial release. Bundles the .deb-based ubiquity installer for
    TMJOs ISOs, since Ubuntu 24.04's default installer is a snap
    (snapd is removed by TMJOs's slim phase).
  * Depends on ubiquity + ubiquity-frontend-gtk only — explicitly
    NOT on ubiquity-slideshow-ubuntu, which requires WebKit2GTK
    and crashed the installer on v1.3.0-1 ISO.
  * Postinst cleans /root/.config/pulse and /root/.cache to avoid
    permission-denied errors during ubiquity's rsync to target.
    These dirs get populated by PulseAudio during the Cubic build
    and then break the install pass.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 22:00:00 -0300
